node.text: @talkeetnaair took me on one of the rides of my life in Alaska. believe it or not, this is a glacier that stretches for miles and miles from the mountains of Denali down towards the ocean near Anchorage. it doesn’t reach the ocean these days due to global warming, but they say it did before. just amazing the sheer mass of this place. you can’t grasp it really until you get in the air and fly around. big thanks again to Talkeetna Air for the ride, education, and photo time 🤙 be back soon

I want to thank everyone who came out to one of my shows on this tour. The Sun and Moon project is something that has been on my mind for awhile and i’m really happy with how it turned out, and i’m stoked to bridge the 2 styles of music I love to produce together. thank you for supporting my musical journey thus far. i’ll be taking a touring hiatus for a while now, and focusing on more production. to be totally transparent, i’ve struggled for the past few years to put out new music and projects due to touring so much. I love playing shows, but it’s definitely worn on me. it’s not all sunshine and rainbows and a party. it’s hard work, sleepless nights on the road, long nights in the studio, compromising of eating healthy food and cooking at home, living out of a suitcase, 6am flights to the next city for another show, etc etc the list goes on. but it’s all been worth it ❤️❤️❤️ I love the music, and i’m here for that not for the party. the music, the community, and the people are what has carried me through the journey of this music industry. i’ll be back next year sometime to play select shows, but expect a lot more music from me, and i’m hoping it’s my best work yet 😘 the Sun and Moon album is dropping shortly (after project and DAW issues it’s now finished) .

I was shooting this shot without any humans, and then I noticed this family crossed from right to left in my view and I made a split decision to time it when they lined up with the walkway. turned out really cool with the lighting so I ran up to them and showed them the shot and told them I would send it to them. sometimes when you least expect it you get an added bonus to your photo. I enjoy this one in particular because with the family in the photo it also adds to the perspective to get a feel for the size of the valley ❤️

Field of Light // One of the most amazing art installations i’ve ever seen. so happy I went out of the way on this trip to go shoot this place. close to 60,000 solar powered lights that stretch for acres. the magic happens as the sun starts to set.... more to come 🔥
